       "[Document(metadata={'producer': 'ReportLab PDF Library - (opensource)', 'creator': '(unspecified)', 'creationdate': '2026-03-13T11:33:08+00:00', 'author': '(anonymous)', 'keywords': '', 'moddate': '2026-03-13T11:33:08+00:00', 'subject': '(unspecified)', 'title': '(anonymous)', 'trapped': '/False', 'source': 'wastage_of_plastic.pdf', 'total_pages': 4, 'page': 0, 'page_label': '1'}, page_content='Wastage of Plastic\\nPlastic has become one of the most widely used materials in modern society. It is lightweight,\\ndurable, and inexpensive, which makes it useful for packaging, household items, electronics, and\\nmany other products. However, the excessive use and improper disposal of plastic have created a\\nmajor environmental problem known as plastic wastage. Every year, millions of tons of plastic\\nwaste are produced around the world. A large portion of this waste is single■use plastic such as\\nplastic bags, bottles, straws, and packaging. These products are often used for only a few minutes\\nbut can take hundreds of years to decompose in the environment. One of the biggest issues with\\nplastic waste is that it does not break down easily. Instead of decomposing like organic materials,\\nplastic slowly breaks into smaller pieces called microplastics. These tiny particles can spread\\nthrough soil, rivers, oceans, and even the air, affecting ecosystems and living organisms.'),\n",
       " Document(metadata={'producer': 'ReportLab PDF Library - (opensource)', 'creator': '(unspecified)', 'creationdate': '2026-03-13T11:33:08+00:00', 'author': '(anonymous)', 'keywords': '', 'moddate': '2026-03-13T11:33:08+00:00', 'subject': '(unspecified)', 'title': '(anonymous)', 'trapped': '/False', 'source': 'wastage_of_plastic.pdf', 'total_pages': 4, 'page': 1, 'page_label': '2'}, page_content='Plastic wastage has serious environmental consequences. A large amount of plastic waste ends up\\nin oceans and rivers, where it harms marine life. Sea turtles, fish, and birds often mistake plastic for\\nfood. When they consume plastic, it can block their digestive systems and lead to injury or death.\\nAnother major issue is that plastic pollution damages natural habitats. Beaches, forests, and urban\\nareas are increasingly filled with discarded plastic items. This not only harms wildlife but also affects\\nthe beauty and health of natural environments. In addition, burning plastic waste releases toxic\\ngases into the air. These harmful chemicals can contribute to air pollution and may cause health\\nproblems for humans, including respiratory diseases and other long■term health risks.'),\n",
       " Document(metadata={'producer': 'ReportLab PDF Library - (opensource)', 'creator': '(unspecified)', 'creationdate': '2026-03-13T11:33:08+00:00', 'author': '(anonymous)', 'keywords': '', 'moddate': '2026-03-13T11:33:08+00:00', 'subject': '(unspecified)', 'title': '(anonymous)', 'trapped': '/False', 'source': 'wastage_of_plastic.pdf', 'total_pages': 4, 'page': 2, 'page_label': '3'}, page_content='The causes of plastic wastage are mainly related to human behavior and consumption patterns.\\nOne of the biggest causes is the overuse of single■use plastic products. Many everyday items such\\nas water bottles, food wrappers, and shopping bags are designed to be used once and then thrown\\naway. Another cause is poor waste management systems in many parts of the world. When plastic\\nwaste is not properly collected, recycled, or disposed of, it often ends up in landfills or the natural\\nenvironment. Lack of awareness is also a contributing factor. Many people are not fully aware of the\\nlong■term environmental impact of plastic pollution. Without proper education and awareness,\\nindividuals may continue harmful habits such as littering or excessive plastic consumption.'),\n",
       " Document(metadata={'producer': 'ReportLab PDF Library - (opensource)', 'creator': '(unspecified)', 'creationdate': '2026-03-13T11:33:08+00:00', 'author': '(anonymous)', 'keywords': '', 'moddate': '2026-03-13T11:33:08+00:00', 'subject': '(unspecified)', 'title': '(anonymous)', 'trapped': '/False', 'source': 'wastage_of_plastic.pdf', 'total_pages': 4, 'page': 3, 'page_label': '4'}, page_content='There are several solutions that can help reduce plastic wastage. One of the most effective\\nsolutions is reducing the use of single■use plastics. People can switch to reusable bags, bottles,\\nand containers instead of disposable plastic items. Recycling is another important step. Proper\\nrecycling systems allow plastic materials to be reused and transformed into new products.\\nGovernments and organizations should invest in better recycling infrastructure and encourage\\ncitizens to participate in recycling programs. Education and awareness campaigns can also play a\\ncrucial role. When people understand the harmful effects of plastic pollution, they are more likely to\\nadopt environmentally friendly habits. In conclusion, plastic wastage is a serious global issue that\\naffects the environment, wildlife, and human health. By reducing plastic use, improving waste\\nmanagement, and spreading awareness, society can work together to minimize plastic pollution\\nand protect the planet for future generations.')]"
